                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rx94044/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><hi rend=\"underline\">Not by the Editor</hi>. We indeed discovered that <persName>B.\n                    L. F.</persName> wished to place<lb/> his own labours somewhat prominently\n                before the public; but this we<lb/> did not deem any insult to <persName>Mr\n                    Kalisch</persName>; as little as the statement that<lb/> he was Hazan and\n                Teacher, as we have in our own person filled both<lb/> these functions, and were\n                nevertheless the preacher of the older congregation<lb/> of\n                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> for twenty years, without any other title\n                than Heizan,<lb/> To be <add>?</add> preaching was gratuitous, and was not\n                    <add>?</add> in the<lb/> contract which was drawn up by the managers of the\n                congregation,<lb/> but <add>?</add> there is no insult in one being called the <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">Hazan</hi> of any<lb/> public body, especially in\n                    <placeName>America</placeName> when, until the arrival of<lb/>\n                <persName>Rabbi A. Rice</persName> of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> not long\n                since it was the highest<lb/>\n                <sic>ecclessiastical</sic> title among us. We have borne it for upward of<lb/>\n                twenty one years, and thought it no degradation, though we<lb/> occasionally acted\n                as Rabbi &amp; preached not a few sermons,<lb/> with what success is not for us to\n                say. <add>?</add> we must that<lb/> on friends at <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>\n                will discharge us from any <add>?</add> of<lb/> slighting them or <persName>Mr\n                    Kalisch</persName>, when contributors we have<lb/> from time to time inserted in\n                the Occident <add>?</add> have thing we<lb/> must state, that if <persName>Mr\n                    K</persName> should be attacked hereafter (but<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">not</hi> in the Occident as our work has a higher aim than\n                destroying<lb/> observation,) it will be his own fault for his extremely\n                injurious<lb/> course in the divine case, since he has not <add>?</add> till he<lb/>\n                succeeded in appearing before the public in the Asmonean as the<lb/> accuser of\n                    <persName>Mr Joseph Levy</persName>. For our part we are tired of the\n                controversy<lb/> it is a subject for a <add>שאלה</add> (Question) to the highest\n                authorities in <placeName>Europe</placeName>;<lb/> and we will abide by their\n                decision; but no man who understands<lb/> the nature of Jewish jurisprudence will\n                for a moment contend that<lb/> either Plain dealer, Asmonean or Occident is a proper\n                vehicle to</p>\n            <div>\n                <p>\n                    <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_10_6.pdf\">The above text refers to Occident\n                        Volume 10 No. 6 pages 305 through 308. Click here to view.</ref>\n                </p>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
